						               													<description>This solitaire game is a fan-fiction re-imagining of the story that unfolds in the comic Tales of the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, volume 1, #2, &amp;ldquo;Nobody&amp;rsquo;s Fool&amp;rdquo;, published by Mirage Studios in July 1987.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It consists of a 54-card deck, and it is free to print and play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Take on the roles of the four ninja turtles and their unexpected ally, &amp;ldquo;Nobody&amp;rdquo;.  Break up an unlawful weapons sale, leave evidence of the exchange for the police, and vanish into the night!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game lasts 4 rounds.  In each round, you draft 13 cards from the deck into your hand.  Then, you play these cards from your hand to the tableau and/or use the actions on them in any order that you choose.  The order of card play and the timing of their use is the heart of the puzzle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round has specific objectives that must be met, or you lose.  By the time the last plot card is played, your ninjas and their vigilante friend will have had a busy night.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
